# Plan: Add bash-script "compilation" to the Makefile

## Context

The Makefile at `/home/choudhury/tools/Makefile` already builds thin shell wrappers in `bin/` for each entry in `PY_SCRIPTS` (e.g. `bin/process_flight` → execs `python3 .../process_flight.py "$@"`). The user has added a bash helper at `dev/docker_runner/devcon.sh` and wants the same treatment: build `bin/devcon` (no `.sh`) using the existing wrapper pattern. `~/tools/bin` is already on `PATH`, so the wrapper will be invokable as `devcon` once created.

## Files to modify

- `/home/choudhury/tools/Makefile` — add a parallel pipeline for shell scripts.

## Change

Mirror the Python pipeline with a `SH_SCRIPTS` / `SH_BINS` / `MAKE_SH_WRAPPER` triple, and fold the shell bins into `all`, the duplicate-name guard, and `clean`.

Concretely:

1. Add an interpreter variable next to `PYTHON`:
   ```make
   SH := bash
   ```

2. Add the script list and derived bin list near `PY_SCRIPTS`:
   ```make
   SH_SCRIPTS := \
       dev/docker_runner/devcon.sh

   SH_BINS := $(foreach s,$(SH_SCRIPTS),$(BIN_DIR)/$(notdir $(basename $(s))))
   ```
   `$(basename …)` strips the `.sh`, exactly as it strips `.py` for the Python case, producing `bin/devcon`.

3. Update `all` to depend on both:
   ```make
   all: $(PY_BINS) $(SH_BINS)
   ```

4. Update the duplicate-name guard to consider both lists together, so a `foo.py` and `foo.sh` collision is caught:
   ```make
   ALL_BINS := $(PY_BINS) $(SH_BINS)
   ifneq ($(words $(ALL_BINS)),$(words $(sort $(ALL_BINS))))
   $(error Duplicate executable names detected in PY_SCRIPTS/SH_SCRIPTS)
   endif
   ```

5. Add a wrapper macro parallel to `MAKE_PY_WRAPPER`:
   ```make
   define MAKE_SH_WRAPPER
   $(BIN_DIR)/$(notdir $(basename $(1))): $(1) Makefile | $(BIN_DIR)
   	@printf '%s\n' \
   		'#!/bin/sh' \
   		'exec "$(SH)" "$(abspath $(1))" "$$$$@"' \
   		> $$@
   	@chmod 0755 $$@
   endef

   $(foreach script,$(SH_SCRIPTS),$(eval $(call MAKE_SH_WRAPPER,$(script))))
   ```
   The generated `bin/devcon` will be:
   ```sh
   #!/bin/sh
   exec "bash" "/home/choudhury/tools/dev/docker_runner/devcon.sh" "$@"
   ```
   This matches the Python wrapper shape exactly — only the interpreter changes — and means the wrapper does not depend on `devcon.sh` being marked executable or on its shebang.

6. Update `clean`:
   ```make
   clean:
   	rm -f -- $(PY_BINS) $(SH_BINS)
   ```

## Note worth flagging (not part of the change)

`dev/docker_runner/devcon.sh` currently starts with `#!/usr/bin/env python3`, which looks like a copy-paste from a Python script — the file is actually a bash one-liner. With the proposed wrapper this is harmless (we invoke it via `bash` explicitly), but if `devcon.sh` is ever run directly it will be handed to `python3` and fail. Worth fixing the shebang to `#!/usr/bin/env bash` in a separate edit.

